main event: An unidentified object was observed in Beatrice, Nebraska on 13 August 1956.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 20 minutes,The object was detected via ground control and radar,The object appeared to be 15 to 20 feet in diameter,The object moved to the east at a speed too fast to follow with the eyes,The conclusions suggested it could possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon.
witness description: Details of an observed object reported through radar and visual observation.
